{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, this model offers an effective approach to integrate diverse forms of information, in order to enhance the detection of fake news.",
    "One of the main challenges in disinformation detection is that many models are specifically designed to operate within a particular domain.",
    "In other words, these models are trained on datasets specific to certain domains (e.g., sports or politics), which limits their ability to effectively learn domain-specific features.",
    "Consequently, they may not perform well when applied to data from other domains.",
    "To tackle this challenge, Yuan et al. (2021) proposed a novel domain-adversarial and graph-attention neural network (DAGA-NN) model, which has the capability to learn domain-invariant features of fake news across different events and domains."
  ]
}